Open Exploation - Part 2¶

In this part the exploratory data gathered from part 1 will be further analysed. The goal is to uncover perspectives and patterns between KPIs and locations in order to develop policies that stimulate the right outcomes. The data will be aggregated by location and by KPI.

In [97]:
location = ['A.1', 'A.2', 'A.3', 'A.4', 'A.5']
kpi = ['Total Costs', 'Expected Number of Deaths', 'Expected Evacuation Costs',
      'RfR Total Costs']

# Creating DataFrames specific to every location
db_A1 = pd.DataFrame()
db_A2 = pd.DataFrame()
db_A3 = pd.DataFrame()
db_A4 = pd.DataFrame()
db_A5 = pd.DataFrame()

# Adding location-specific columns to the location-specific DataFrames
db_A1 = db_outcomes.filter(regex=location[0])
db_A2 = db_outcomes.filter(regex=location[1])
db_A3 = db_outcomes.filter(regex=location[2])
db_A4 = db_outcomes.filter(regex=location[3])
db_A5 = db_outcomes.filter(regex=location[4])

# Adding Expected Evacuation Costs 
db_A1 = db_A1.join(db_outcomes[kpi[2]])  
db_A2 = db_A2.join(db_outcomes[kpi[2]])
db_A3 = db_A3.join(db_outcomes[kpi[2]])
db_A4 = db_A4.join(db_outcomes[kpi[2]])
db_A5 = db_A5.join(db_outcomes[kpi[2]])

# Adding RfR Total Costs 
db_A1 = db_A1.join(db_outcomes[kpi[3]])  
db_A2 = db_A2.join(db_outcomes[kpi[3]])
db_A3 = db_A3.join(db_outcomes[kpi[3]])
db_A4 = db_A4.join(db_outcomes[kpi[3]])
db_A5 = db_A5.join(db_outcomes[kpi[3]])
